{"parse":{"title":"Jim Miller (linguist)","pageid":24869243,"revid":821437212,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Jim Miller</b> (born <b>James Edward Miller</b>) is a Professor of <a href=\"/wiki/Cognitive_linguistics\" title=\"Cognitive linguistics\">cognitive linguistics</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Auckland\" title=\"University of Auckland\">University of Auckland</a>, researcher on language <a href=\"/wiki/Syntax\" title=\"Syntax\">syntax</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Semantics\" title=\"Semantics\">semantics</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Standardology\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Standardology\">standardology</a>. In the period of 2003-2007 he was <a href=\"/wiki/Professor_Emeritus\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Professor Emeritus\">Professor Emeritus</a> of Spoken Language at the Department of Theoretical and Applied Linguistics of the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Edinburgh\" title=\"University of Edinburgh\">University of Edinburgh</a>.\n</p><p>In 1965 he received M.A. at the University of Edinburgh in <a href=\"/wiki/Russian_language\" title=\"Russian language\">Russian</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/French_language\" title=\"French language\">French</a>, receiving a Diploma in General Linguistics a year later. He received his Ph.D. on <i>Tense and Aspect in Russian</i> in 1970. <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>After graduation, his main focus of interest for the first 20 years were in <a href=\"/wiki/Grammatical_aspect\" title=\"Grammatical aspect\">aspect</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Grammatical_case\" title=\"Grammatical case\">case</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Transitivity_(grammatical_category)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Transitivity (grammatical category)\">transitivity</a>, as well as various models of the <a href=\"/wiki/Generative_grammar\" title=\"Generative grammar\">generative grammar</a> framework.\n</p><p>In late 1970s he investigated the syntax of <a href=\"/wiki/Scottish_English\" title=\"Scottish English\">Scottish English</a> together with <a href=\"/wiki/Keith_Brown_(linguist)\" title=\"Keith Brown (linguist)\">Keith Brown</a>, which eventually led him to the research of a more general notion of syntax of spontaneous spoken language (English, Russian, and French), as well as the relation of spoken and written language, <a href=\"/wiki/Literacy\" title=\"Literacy\">literacy</a>, and the relationship of language and <a href=\"/wiki/Politics\" title=\"Politics\">politics</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Education\" title=\"Education\">education</a> and identity. As a result of this research, he published a book <i>Spontaneous Spoken Language</i> together with <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Regina_Weinert&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Regina Weinert (page does not exist)\">Regina Weinert</a> in 1998.\n</p><p>His current research interest include speaking, writing and <a href=\"/wiki/Language_acquisition\" title=\"Language acquisition\">language acquisition</a>, as well as topics on spoken language, non-standard language, and typology.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Books\">Books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jim_Miller_(linguist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>Semantics and Syntax: Parallels and Connections</i> (1985)</li>\n<li><i>Syntax: A Linguistic Introduction to Sentence Structure</i> (1992, with E K Brown, James V Miller)</li>\n<li><i>Spontaneous Spoken Language&#160;: Syntax and Discourse</i> (1998, with Regina Weinert)</li>\n<li><i>An Introduction to English Syntax</i> (2000)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jim_Miller_(linguist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Edward, Miller, James (1970). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.era.lib.ed.ac.uk/handle/1842/17417\">\"Tense and aspect in Russian\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Tense+and+aspect+in+Russian&amp;rft.date=1970&amp;rft.aulast=Edward&amp;rft.aufirst=Miller%2C+James&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.era.lib.ed.ac.uk%2Fhandle%2F1842%2F17417&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJim+Miller+%28linguist%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ling.ed.ac.uk/~jmiller/\">Personal Webpage</a></li></ul>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q16732609&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th id=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q16732609&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" scope=\"row\" class=\"navbox-group\" style=\"width:1%\"><a href=\"/wiki/Help:Authority_control\" title=\"Help:Authority control\">Authority control</a> <a href=\"https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q16732609\" title=\"Edit this at Wikidata\"><img alt=\"Edit this at Wikidata\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thu